name: Jeff Irion
body:
## About Me

I received my Ph.D. in Applied Math from UC Davis in December 2015.  


## Code, Projects, & Repos

### [My Udacity Coursework](http://jefflirion.github.io/udacity/)
Assignments and projects that I've done for data science courses offered by Udacity.  

### [Multiscale Transforms for Signals on Graphs (MTSG) Toolbox for MATLAB](https://github.com/JeffLIrion/MTSG_Toolbox)
This toolbox contains implementations of the transforms and methods that I developed during my graduate research.  It can be used to easily reproduce figures from several publications as well as my dissertation.  

### [Math Course Notes](http://jefflirion.github.io/Math-Course-Notes/)
Notes from various courses that I took at UC Davis.
